article.headline: Duquesne 94, Radford 75
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Aaron Jackson scored a career-high 36 points to lead Duquesne to a 94-75 victory over Radford on Wednesday night. Jackson made 15 of 17 field goals and was 1-for-1 from the free-throw line one week after scoring a season-low six points against No. 3 Pittsburgh. The Dukes (5-2) went on a 10-0 run midway through the first half to break open a 22-21 game and took a 51-40 lead into halftime. Radford (3-5) drew within six points at 76-70 with 5:43 left, but Duquesne scored seven straight points, including a 3-pointer by Jackson. Damian Saunders added 11 points and Bill Clark had 10 for the Dukes. Martell McDuffy led the Highlanders with 21 points, while Artsiom Parakhouski had a double-double with 17 points and 20 rebounds -- nearly half of Radford's 43 total rebounds. Kenny Thomas added 14 points and Joey Lynch-Flohr had 12.
